# AgentBox Firewall Configuration
# Location: ~/.agentbox/firewall.conf
#
# This file controls which network services the AgentBox container can access.
# The firewall is enabled by default to provide network isolation.
#
# FORMAT
# ------
# domain [options]
#
# OPTIONS
# -------
# critical   - Container fails to start if this service can't be resolved
# wide-net   - Allows entire /24 subnet (for services with frequently changing IPs)
#
# DISABLING THE FIREWALL
# -----------------------
# For a single run:    AGENTBOX_FIREWALL=disabled agentbox
# Permanently:         export AGENTBOX_FIREWALL=disabled  (add to shell profile)
#
# HARDCODED RANGES
# ----------------
# GitHub IP ranges are always allowed (hardcoded, not via DNS) to ensure
# reliable access even if DNS resolution fails.

# ============================================================================
# CRITICAL SERVICES (container fails if these can't be resolved)
# ============================================================================

github.com critical
api.github.com critical
api.anthropic.com critical

# ============================================================================
# PACKAGE REGISTRIES
# ============================================================================

# npm
registry.npmjs.org

# Maven (wide-net due to frequent IP changes)
repo.maven.apache.org wide-net
repo1.maven.org wide-net

# Gradle
plugins.gradle.org

# ============================================================================
# CUSTOM SERVICES (add your own below)
# ============================================================================

# Examples:
# my-api.example.com
# my-cdn.example.com wide-net
# my-auth-server.example.com critical
